\n<In-car news>\C[24]Good morning, this is MSGK Morning News.

\n<In-car news>\C[24]Today's weather is cloudy, and there is a
possibility of rain tomorrow--

\n<In-car news>\C[24]A man living in Tokyo was arrested early
yesterday morning on suspicion of quasi-forced
indecent assault against a woman in her 30s by
mixing sleeping pills into a drink at a restaurant
in Sakutsuki City.
車内2

\n<In-car news>\C[24]--There have been multiple reports of
symptoms suspected to be mental disorders in the
surrounding area, and the city has requested the
Ministry of the Environment--
Actor03
\n<\N[3]>Oh... what's this...?

Headquarters orders. Upon arrival at the site,
promptly begin the investigation and make every
effort to quickly identify and resolve the cause.
Actor03

\n<\N[3]>...Being suddenly dispatched and told something
like that, there's no way I would know things that
the forensic science laboratory knows...

\n<In-car news>The crime rate in \C[24]—— has been on the rise in
recent years, prompting the police to establish an
investigation headquarters———
Actor03

Yesterday, I suddenly received a transfer order.
There have been frequent occurrences of a
phenomenon called madness in the vicinity of
Sakutsuki City (Tachigori).

It's not easy to investigate the phenomenon
occurring in a distant place from my jurisdiction,
even though I've been dispatched for that
investigation.

However, according to rumors, several of the
mobilized investigators have also shown similar
symptoms and are now hospitalized in a mental
institution.
